  <!--
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  A S S I S T A N T   A R M   (bimanual mode)

  A second Franka Panda arm (7-DOF, no hand) is composed via
  MjSpec.attach() with prefix "assistant_" at position (1.0, 0, 0.18)
  on the opposite side of the surgical table, raised above table height. The assistant arm has
  a flat pad end-effector for pressing tissue, enabling bimanual
  coordination where one arm sutures while the other stabilizes.

  The BimanualStabilizeTissue skill controls the assistant arm through
  a 3-phase execution: approach (0-40%), descend (40-70%), press/hold (70-100%).

  BIMANUAL_SUTURE_WORKFLOW:
    1. bimanual_stabilize — assistant arm presses tissue
    2. grasp_needle — primary arm approaches and grasps
    3. orient_needle — rotate to 45-degree insertion angle
    4. insert_needle — drive through tissue
    5. pull_suture — retract, drawing suture
    6. regrasp_needle — release, reposition, regrasp
    7. tie_knot — wrap, pull, tighten

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  E Q U A L I T Y   C O N S T R A I N T S   (48 total)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  <equality>
    ── Spring-mass tissue: 5×4 sphere grid linked by CONNECT (43) ──
    ── Horizontal neighbours (15):
    <connect name="tissue_eq_r0_c0" body1="tissue_s_0_0" body2="tissue_s_0_1"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_r0_c1" body1="tissue_s_0_1" body2="tissue_s_0_2"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_r0_c2" body1="tissue_s_0_2" body2="tissue_s_0_3"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    ── ... (rows 1-4, same pattern: tissue_s_r_c ↔ tissue_s_r_{c+1}) ──

    ── Vertical neighbours (16):
    <connect name="tissue_eq_d0_c0" body1="tissue_s_0_0" body2="tissue_s_1_0"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_d0_c1" body1="tissue_s_0_1" body2="tissue_s_1_1"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_d0_c2" body1="tissue_s_0_2" body2="tissue_s_1_2"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_d0_c3" body1="tissue_s_0_3" body2="tissue_s_1_3"
             solref="0.02 0.8" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    ── ... (rows 1-3, same pattern: tissue_s_r_c ↔ tissue_s_{r+1}_c) ──

    ── Diagonal stabilisers (12):
    <connect name="tissue_eq_diag0_c0" body1="tissue_s_0_0" body2="tissue_s_1_1"
             solref="0.03 0.6" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_diag0_c1" body1="tissue_s_0_1" body2="tissue_s_1_2"
             solref="0.03 0.6" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    <connect name="tissue_eq_diag0_c2" body1="tissue_s_0_2" body2="tissue_s_1_3"
             solref="0.03 0.6" solimp="0.1 0.95 0.05 0.5 0.5"/>
    ── ... (3 more rows, same pattern: tissue_s_r_c ↔ tissue_s_{r+1}_{c+1}) ──

    ── Corner anchors (4): weld corner spheres to the table ──
    <weld name="tissue_anchor_0_0" body1="tissue_s_0_0" body2="table"
          solref="0.01 1.0" solimp="0.8 0.95 0.01 0.5 0.5"/>
    <weld name="tissue_anchor_0_3" body1="tissue_s_0_3" body2="table"
          solref="0.01 1.0" solimp="0.8 0.95 0.01 0.5 0.5"/>
    <weld name="tissue_anchor_4_0" body1="tissue_s_4_0" body2="table"
          solref="0.01 1.0" solimp="0.8 0.95 0.01 0.5 0.5"/>
    <weld name="tissue_anchor_4_3" body1="tissue_s_4_3" body2="table"
          solref="0.01 1.0" solimp="0.8 0.95 0.01 0.5 0.5"/>

    ── Needle grasp weld (1): INACTIVE by default; activated by ──
    ── activate_needle_weld() on finger-needle contact detection  ──
    <weld name="needle_grasp_weld" body1="hand_palm" body2="needle"
          active="false" solref="0.02 1.0" solimp="0.95 0.99 0.001 0.5 2.0"/>
  </equality>
  -->

